# Planner Builder Rules

## Runtime

- Treat `planner-server` as the canonical Builder runtime.
- Do not target bare `npm run dev --prefix planner-solid` for Fusion work.
- Use the same-origin app runtime at `http://127.0.0.1:4174`.
- If the app is not already running, prefer the repo wrapper `make builder-launch`.

## Build Model

- Planner serves built frontend assets from `planner-server`.
- When frontend code changes, rebuild `planner-solid` before expecting Builder to see those changes.
- Keep Builder launch and local runtime assumptions aligned with `builder.config.json`.

## Local AI Safety

- Default Builder-connected local work to the deterministic Planner mock profile unless a human explicitly asks for live provider CLIs.
- The canonical mock setting is `PLANNER_LLM_MOCK=full_pipeline`.
- Do not require real Claude, Gemini, or Codex subscriptions just to make Builder local workflows function.

## Repo Boundaries

- Treat Fusion project runtime settings, Builder CMS content, and Builder DSI as separate surfaces.
- Do not describe Builder CMS sync as if it updates Fusion project runtime settings.
- Prefer committed repo configuration and instruction files over one-off chat guidance.

## Change Discipline

- Keep edits bounded to the task at hand.
- Avoid destructive git operations.
- Do not edit generated build artifacts under `planner-solid/dist`.
- Prefer updating source files, Builder config files, and documented repo scripts.
